{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013s2QgSFM9m1ybWDgETbj2G","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant\n3\tdate: 2026-05-27\n4\ttarget_release: 0.7.0\n5\tdesc: Binary quantization (bit[768]) plus f32 rerank on the existing sqlite-vec extension, with metadata + partition_key schema migration, as the data-encoding change that closes AC-013 within the proposed 80 / 300 ms latency envelope. AC-019 keeps its existing 10× bound and is collaterally re-measured under the new query path. Architectural-lever accounting reaffirmed: PCACHE2 remains the 0.7.0 architectural lever; this is a data-encoding change.\n6\tblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323 (read_search_in_tx hot SQL; Pack 2 rewrite); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846 (_fathomdb_vector_rows writer insert; Pack 1 double-write); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3278-3283 (vector_default CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE; Pack 1 schema migration); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107 (register_sqlite_vec_extension; unchanged but inspected); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260 (_fathomdb_embedder_profiles; UNCHANGED — embedder contract preserved); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2174,2242 (writer-loop pins; unchanged); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150 (AC013_BUDGET_P50/P99 re-pin in Pack 2); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:487 (ac_013_vector_retrieval_latency); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:609 (ac_019_mixed_retrieval_stress_workload_tail); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs new ac_NNN_recall_at_10 test (Pack 2); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml:18 (sqlite-vec pin; stays =0.1.7); dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md (numeric lock-flip target, post Pack 2); dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md (post-0.7.0 ANN follow-ups)\n7\tstatus: draft, HITL-required\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# ADR-0.7.0 — Vector binary quantization (Pack 1 + Pack 2)\n11\t\n12\t**Status:** draft, HITL-required.\n13\t\n14\tThis ADR records the data-encoding decision that closes AC-013\n15\twithin the proposed 80 / 300 ms envelope in 0.7.0. AC-019 is\n16\tcollaterally re-measured under the new query path — its existing\n17\t10× stress-bound is expected to improve proportionally but its\n18\tbudget shape is unchanged and its numeric row in the budgets ADR\n19\tremains a placeholder pending the post-Pack-2 canonical-CI run\n20\t(see § 6). It is paired with — and feeds into — the numeric\n21\tlock-flip that will be made post-Pack-2 against\n22\t`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`. That ADR\n23\tremains the budget owner; this ADR commits the architectural shape\n24\tthat makes those budgets reachable.\n25\t\n26\t## 1. Problem\n27\t\n28\tCanonical-CI measurement on 2026-05-27 under the locked\n29\tW4.1-stacked-O1 (`L-Y1+L-Y2+L-B5+L-B4+L-D1-pcache2-O1`) stack\n30\t(`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`)\n31\treports AC-013 at **p50 = 2048 ms, p99 = 2327 ms** on the\n32\tN = 1,000,000 / dim 768 f32 fixture seeded by `VaryingEmbedder`\n33\t(`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:296` and\n34\t`:317`). AC-019 stress p99 = 8388 ms under bound 20964 ms; the\n35\tbound is met today but the underlying per-query cost is the same\n36\thot path.\n37\t\n38\tThe proposed budgets in\n39\t`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md` are\n40\t**80 ms p50 / 300 ms p99**. The measurement is therefore\n41\t**~25–40× over** the budget envelope. The current\n42\t`AC013_BUDGET_P50 = 50ms` / `AC013_BUDGET_P99 = 200ms` constants in\n43\t`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150` are\n44\tthe unindexed-path-pre-lock values; the revised budgets ADR drafts\n45\t80 / 300 ms but they have not yet been pinned in the test, by\n46\tdesign (the re-pin is itself the Pack 2 RED gate).\n47\t\n48\t**Root cause.** The hot SQL at\n49\t`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323`\n50\t\n51\t```\n52\tSELECT rowid FROM vector_default\n53\tWHERE embedding MATCH vec_f32(?1)\n54\tORDER BY distance\n55\tLIMIT 10\n56\t```\n57\t\n58\tdrives a per-query O(N) brute-force scan over the\n59\t`vector_default` vec0 table declared at\n60\t`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3278-3283` as\n61\t`USING vec0(embedding float[<dim>])` — i.e. a single global f32\n62\ttable with no metadata columns, no partition keys, no auxiliary\n63\tindex. At N = 1 M × dim 768 × 4 B that is 3.0 GB of memory\n64\tstreamed per query; the observed 2048 ms p50 corresponds to\n65\t~1.5 GB/s, which sits at the single-thread memory-read ceiling\n66\ton the canonical AMD EPYC 7763 runner. No SQLite engine knob can\n67\tmove this — the bytes-per-row × rows-per-query product is the\n68\tfloor. To close the gate we must either shrink the bytes per row,\n69\tshrink the row count visited per query, or both.\n70\t\n71\tCross-reference: `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`\n72\t§ \"Problem restated\" through § \"Tier 1 combined estimate\" enumerates\n73\tthe lever surface; the present ADR commits to the Tier-1 #4 +\n74\tTier-1 #1/#2 bundle as the load-bearing decision.\n75\t\n76\t## 2. Decision\n77\t\n78\tAdopt the following, to ship in two packs within the 0.7.0 release\n79\tline (Pack 1 then Pack 2; pack boundary is for review granularity,\n80\tnot release-boundary):\n81\t\n82\t1. **Binary quantization** of the f32 embedding into a sibling\n83\t   `bit[768]` column on the existing `vector_default` vec0 table\n84\t   (Pack 1.1 default per\n85\t   `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`\n86\t   § 1.1). The bit column is computed via sqlite-vec's\n87\t   `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)` and written inside the same\n88\t   writer transaction as the existing f32 insert. Sibling-table\n89\t   fallback (`vector_default_bin`) is selected only if the\n90\t   sibling-column shape hits the vec0 metadata column limit\n91\t   (16 cols). The f32 `embedding` column is **retained** for\n92\t   the rerank phase and for the recall-floor ground-truth pass —\n93\t   it has two jobs after Pack 1.\n94\t\n95\t2. **Two-phase query** (Pack 2): bit-KNN top-K=64 candidates →\n96\t   f32 rerank → top-10. The exact SQL shape (subject to the\n97\t   sqlite-vec syntax confirmation called out in\n98\t   `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § 2.2)\n99\t   replaces the single-phase scan at\n100\t   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323`. K is\n101\t   a named constant / config knob so future tuning is cheap; the\n102\t   K = 64 default is taken from the Kyle Howells and Cohere\n103\t   binary-quant benches cited in\n104\t   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #4.\n105\t\n106\t3. **Schema extension shipped on the same migration** (Pack 1):\n107\t   - `source_type TEXT` as a vec0 **partition_key**\n108\t     (HITL-locked 2026-05-27 in\n109\t     `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`; cardinality ~6:\n110\t     email, article, paper, meeting, note, todo). Maps from the\n111\t     existing chunk-record vector kind at write time\n112\t     (deterministic 1:1 mapping for the current single-kind\n113\t     fixture; `source_type` is the authoritative going-forward\n114\t     vocabulary).\n115\t   - Additional metadata columns (`kind`, `created_at`, `tags`,\n116\t     `project_mentions`, …) populated from the existing chunk\n117\t     record. Per HITL Q5 in\n118\t     `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` and\n119\t     `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` Tier 1 #1,\n120\t     descriptive retrieval filters live in metadata columns +\n121\t     WHERE predicates, not in partition keys. The vec0 limit is\n122\t     16 metadata columns; the Pack 1 schema MUST budget headroom.\n123\t\n124\t4. **Recall floor: ≥ 0.90 recall@10** vs f32 brute-force ground\n125\t   truth on the AC-013 fixture\n126\t   (`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`,\n127\t   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § HITL responses #1).\n128\t   Enforced by a new perf-gates test (`ac_NNN_recall_at_10`)\n129\t   landed RED in Pack 2 before the query rewrite. Ground truth\n130\t   is computed at test-setup via a one-pass brute-force scan\n131\t   through the retained f32 column — single corpus, two jobs.\n132\t\n133\t5. **sqlite-vec pin stays `=0.1.7`**\n134\t   (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml:18`). 0.1.7\n135\t   already ships `bit[N]` and `vec_quantize_binary` per the\n136\t   sqlite-vec release notes\n137\t   (`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` Tier 1 #4\n138\t   citation). Bump to `=0.1.9` is allowed in Pack 1 **only if\n139\t   needed** for constraint-column refinements; not required and\n140\t   not recommended without justification.\n141\t\n142\t6. **Embedder unchanged.** The `EmbedderIdentity` contract,\n143\t   `VaryingEmbedder`, and the profile-pinning logic at\n144\t   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260` are\n145\t   not touched. HITL Q2 in\n146\t   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § HITL responses\n147\t   locked: KEEP existing embedder. Tier-1 #3 (smaller\n148\t   embeddings) and Tier-1 #5 (matryoshka) are out of scope\n149\t   for 0.7.0.\n150\t\n151\t7. **Single-writer + projection-cursor contracts preserved.**\n152\t   Both column inserts commit in the same writer transaction at\n153\t   the `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near\n154\t   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846`. The\n155\t   writer-loop pins at `:2174` and `:2242` are not touched.\n156\t   AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 behavior is preserved.\n157\t\n158\t## 3. Alternatives considered (and rejected)\n159\t\n160\tEach alternative below was considered against the AC-013 gap; the\n161\tresearch doc carries the long-form analysis.\n162\t\n163\t- **Vectorlite (HNSW SQLite extension).** Mechanism: load a\n164\t  separate `USING vectorlite(...)` virtual table backed by an\n165\t  HNSW graph stored in shadow tables. Rejected because the\n166\t  upstream has had no release since 2024-08-19, has no\n167\t  published 1 M × 768 benchmark, and counts as a structural\n168\t  architectural lever stacked on top of PCACHE2 — violates the\n169\t  one-architectural-lever-per-release rule. Cited:\n170\t  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 2.\n171\t\n172\t- **sqlite-vec ANN alpha (v0.1.10-alpha.1).** Mechanism: use\n173\t  the upstream-experimental ANN indices (`rescore`, `ivf`,\n174\t  `DiskANN`). Rejected because the release is alpha-tagged and\n175\t  upstream classifies it as not production-ready. Cited:\n176\t  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3,\n177\t  sqlite-vec releases.\n178\t\n179\t- **Rust-side `usearch` / `instant-distance`.** Mechanism:\n180\t  pull KNN out of SQLite into a Rust-side ANN library and\n181\t  rebuild the search verb around it. Rejected because the\n182\t  blast radius (leaving SQLite for the KNN step, snapshot /\n183\t  freshness handshake redesign, AC-017 cursor-freshness\n184\t  re-derivation) is far larger than two packs of in-place\n185\t  schema + query work, and the data-encoding lever closes the\n186\t  gap without it. Cited:\n187\t  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3 (integration\n188\t  shape C).\n189\t\n190\t- **Embedder swap (dim reduction 768 → 384 or 256).**\n191\t  Mechanism: replace `VaryingEmbedder` with a smaller embedder\n192\t  to shrink bytes-per-row. Rejected by HITL Q2 lock 2026-05-27:\n193\t  keep existing embedder. Rationale: switching embedders\n194\t  requires a profile rotation through\n195\t  `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles` and a corpus rebuild\n196\t  (writer-cooperation cost), and even at dim 128 the\n197\t  arithmetic-only saving is ~6× — well short of the ~25–40×\n198\t  gap. Cited:\n199\t  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #3,\n200\t  § HITL responses.\n201\t\n202\t- **Partitioning alone (metadata prefilter / partition_key\n203\t  without quantization).** Mechanism: keep the f32 column,\n204\t  add `source_type` partition_key + metadata columns, push\n205\t  filters into the WHERE clause. Rejected as load-bearing:\n206\t  the AC-013 fixture is single-kind, so partitioning yields\n207\t  zero benefit at the gate. Partitioning is **kept** as a\n208\t  bundled deliverable in Pack 1 because it is the correct\n209\t  shape for real workloads and avoids a second migration in\n210\t  0.7.1 — but it does not close the gate on its own. Cited:\n211\t  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #1, #2.\n212\t\n213\t## 4. Consequences\n214\t\n215\t- **Schema change (Pack 1).** `vector_default` gains the\n216\t  `embedding_bin bit[768]` column, the `source_type` vec0\n217\t  partition_key, and additional metadata columns (within the\n218\t  vec0 16-column budget). Migration is a one-pass\n219\t  `INSERT … SELECT vec_quantize_binary(embedding) FROM\n220\t  vector_default` populating the bit column for the existing\n221\t  corpus. Migration cost: ~3 GB read + ~96 MB write on the\n222\t  1 M-row test corpus; ~64 s on the dev box per the handoff\n223\t  estimate, well under the workflow timeout.\n224\t\n225\t- **Ingest cost (Pack 1).** The writer at the\n226\t  `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near\n227\t  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846` performs\n228\t  a single additional `vec_quantize_binary()` and one extra\n229\t  column write per row inside the same writer transaction.\n230\t  No new commit; no new lock; no new SQLite handle. The\n231\t  single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contract is\n232\t  preserved bit-for-bit. Storage grows by ~3 % (96 B per row\n233\t  on top of the 3072 B f32 footprint).\n234\t\n235\t- **Query-path rewrite (Pack 2).** Replace\n236\t  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323` with\n237\t  the two-phase shape outlined in\n238\t  `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § 2.2.\n239\t  No change to the writer side, no change to the projection-\n240\t  cursor handshake, no change to `register_sqlite_vec_extension`\n241\t  at `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107`. K = 64\n242\t  is named as a constant for future tuning.\n243\t\n244\t- **Recall floor enforced as a RED test.** A new perf-gates\n245\t  test (e.g. `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`) computes brute-force f32\n246\t  ground truth at test-setup against the retained f32 column,\n247\t  runs the production search path, and asserts\n248\t  `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` on the AC-013 fixture. Lands RED in\n249\t  Pack 2.1 alongside the latency budget re-pin\n250\t  (`tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150` → 80 / 300 ms) and must\n251\t  remain RED at canonical-CI N = 1 M scale until Pack 2.2's\n252\t  query rewrite lands. Both gates GREEN at canonical-CI is\n253\t  the Pack 2 close criterion.\n254\t\n255\t- **AC-019 carry.** The existing 10× bound on AC-019 stays\n256\t  unchanged; the same two-phase query shape benefits AC-019\n257\t  proportionally. AC-019 is expected to improve substantially\n258\t  but no new bound is pinned here.\n259\t\n260\t- **AC-012 / AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 unchanged.** The\n261\t  writer-loop pins (`:2174`, `:2242`), the embedder profile\n262\t  table, and the reader-pool concurrency surface are all\n263\t  untouched. Pack 1 changes schema but not query semantics, so\n264\t  these tests stay GREEN through both packs.\n265\t\n266\t- **Post-0.7.0 follow-ups.** Graph-index ANN (vectorlite,\n267\t  sqlite-vec ANN alpha, Rust-side `usearch`) and\n268\t  matryoshka / smaller-embedder work are tracked in\n269\t  `dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md` for 0.7.1+ if real-workload\n270\t  telemetry shows the binary-quant scan is insufficient.\n271\t\n272\t## 5. Architectural-lever accounting\n273\t\n274\tThe 0.7.0 architectural lever is **`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2`**, locked\n275\tby `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md`. The decision\n276\tin § 2 of this ADR is a **data-encoding change** (schema +\n277\tquantization function + two-phase SQL), not a second architectural\n278\tlever:\n279\t\n280\t- It does not change the SQLite build, the SQLite vendor, the WAL\n281\t  format, or the page-cache allocator.\n282\t- It does not change the reader-pool topology, the writer-lock\n283\t  shape, the projection-cursor contract, or the snapshot-freshness\n284\t  contract.\n285\t- It does not change the embedder identity or the profile-pinning\n286\t  protocol.\n287\t- It changes only the bytes stored per row in the vec0 table and\n288\t  the SQL the reader emits against it.\n289\t\n290\tThis disposition is reaffirmed verbatim from\n291\t`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § \"Architectural-lever\n292\taccounting\". The HITL doc records the same call.\n293\t\n294\t**Fallback.** If a future reviewer (codex or HITL) counts\n295\tbinary-quant + rerank as a second architectural lever stacked on\n296\tPCACHE2, the agreed fallback per the handoff and the research doc\n297\tis to ship **Pack 1 only in 0.7.0** (schema migration + ingest\n298\tdouble-write; no reader behavior change; AC-013 stays at\n299\t2048 / 2327 ms) and slip **Pack 2 to 0.7.1** (query rewrite + RED\n300\ttests + lock-flip). The Pack 1-only shape preserves the on-disk\n301\tshape for the future Pack 2 cutover and avoids a second migration.\n302\tEscalation trigger is called out in\n303\t`dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § \"Open\n304\titems the implementing agent should escalate to HITL\".\n305\t\n306\t## 6. Open questions / HITL gates\n307\t\n308\t- **Final numeric AC-013 / AC-019 budgets.** The 80 / 300 ms\n309\t  numbers in § 1 are the proposed envelope from\n310\t  `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`; the\n311\t  final pinned values land after the P2-CANONICAL run, HITL\n312\t  signs the numeric budgets, and the lock-flip is applied to the\n313\t  budgets ADR. The Pack 2 perf-gates re-pin\n314\t  (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`)\n315\t  uses 80 / 300 ms initially; HITL may tighten by ~10 % headroom\n316\t  against the measured numbers at lock time.\n317\t\n318\t- **K-value selection.** Default K = 64 from the binary-quant\n319\t  literature. If the recall-floor test falls below 0.90 at K = 64\n320\t  on canonical-CI scale, escalate before Pack 2 GREEN-test commit\n321\t  (per `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`\n322\t  § \"Open items\"). K may need to rise to 128 or 256; the choice\n323\t  is documented in the closing slice JSON and reflected in the\n324\t  named constant.\n325\t\n326\t- **vec0 metadata column budget.** The vec0 16-column cap\n327\t  constrains the Pack 1 schema. If the desired metadata schema\n328\t  (including future fields for the corpus / API work tracked\n329\t  separately) cannot fit alongside the partition_key + bit\n330\t  column, escalate before Pack 1 schema design freezes. Fallback\n331\t  is the sibling-table shape (`vector_default_bin`) called out\n332\t  in § 2 / Pack 1.1.\n333\t\n334\t- **`vec_quantize_binary()` input expectations.** `VaryingEmbedder`\n335\t  produces L2-normalised f32 vectors\n336\t  (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:322-326`),\n337\t  and the research note records the same\n338\t  (`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md:164-165`). Binary\n339\t  quantization via `vec_quantize_binary()` is a sign-pattern\n340\t  transform that is invariant to positive scaling, so L2 norm\n341\t  itself is not load-bearing, but the function's exact input\n342\t  contract (signed-zero handling, NaN behaviour) has not been\n343\t  validated against `VaryingEmbedder` output. If sqlite-vec 0.1.7's\n344\t  `vec_quantize_binary()` rejects the f32 blobs produced by the\n345\t  current writer path or returns degenerate bit patterns, escalate\n346\t  before Pack 1 ingest changes land (per the handoff § \"Open\n347\t  items\"). The fixture concentrates mass on 6 of 768 coordinates\n348\t  (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:317`),\n349\t  which is atypically friendly to sign-pattern quantisation —\n350\t  HITL is owed the note that AC-013's recall headroom may\n351\t  overstate real-workload headroom.\n352\t\n353\t## 7. Status / next actions\n354\t\n355\t- **Status: `draft, HITL-required`.** No lock-flip happens in this\n356\t  ADR until canonical-CI is GREEN at the re-pinned budgets and\n357\t  the recall floor and HITL signs the numeric budgets in\n358\t  `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`.\n359\t\n360\t- **Immediate next slice.** Orchestrator spawns a codex reviewer\n361\t  on this ADR draft, then promotes the verdict per\n362\t  `dev/design/orchestration.md` § 4. If review is PASS, Pack 1\n363\t  schema-migration + ingest-double-write slice is next.\n364\t\n365\t- **Lock-flip sequencing.** Per the handoff § \"Done = ?\", this\n366\t  ADR moves to `status: locked` only after: Pack 1 lands;\n367\t  Pack 2 lands; canonical-CI dispatch shows AC-013 GREEN at the\n368\t  re-pinned 80 / 300 ms (or HITL-revised) budgets; the new\n369\t  recall-floor test is GREEN at ≥ 0.90; AC-019 verdict is\n370\t  re-measured under the new query path; HITL signs off on the\n371\t  numeric budgets in the revised-budgets ADR. Lock-flip is\n372\t  orchestrator's; this draft does not flip prematurely.\n373\t\n374\t## Citations\n375\t\n376\t- `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`\n377\t  (this ADR's mandating handoff; § Step 0 enumerates the\n378\t  must-cover items).\n379\t- `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` (HITL-RESPONDED;\n380\t  Tier 1 / 2 / 3 catalogue; Pack 1 / 2 split locked).\n381\t- `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` (HITL decision\n382\t  record: recall floor 0.90 @ k=10; `source_type` partition_key;\n383\t  cardinality ~6; sqlite-vec 0.1.7).\n384\t- `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md` (PCACHE2 is\n385\t  the 0.7.0 architectural lever; pattern reference for this\n386\t  ADR's structure).\n387\t- `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`\n388\t  (numeric budget owner; lock-flip target post-Pack-2).\n389\t- `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`\n390\t  (canonical-CI measurement: p50 = 2048 ms, p99 = 2327 ms at\n391\t  N = 1 M, W4.1-stacked-O1 stack, 2026-05-27).\n392\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323` (hot\n393\t  SQL; Pack 2 rewrite site).\n394\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846`\n395\t  (`_fathomdb_vector_rows` writer insert; Pack 1 double-write\n396\t  site).\n397\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3278-3283`\n398\t  (`vector_default` CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE; Pack 1 schema\n399\t  migration site).\n400\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107`\n401\t  (`register_sqlite_vec_extension`; inspected, unchanged).\n402\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260`\n403\t  (`_fathomdb_embedder_profiles`; UNCHANGED — embedder identity\n404\t  contract preserved).\n405\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`\n406\t  (`AC013_BUDGET_P50` / `AC013_BUDGET_P99`; Pack 2 re-pin\n407\t  target).\n408\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:487`\n409\t  (`ac_013_vector_retrieval_latency`).\n410\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:609`\n411\t  (`ac_019_mixed_retrieval_stress_workload_tail`).\n412\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml:18`\n413\t  (`sqlite-vec = \"=0.1.7\"`).\n414\t- sqlite-vec binary quantization guide:\n415\t  https://alexgarcia.xyz/sqlite-vec/guides/binary-quant.html\n416\t- sqlite-vec API reference (DeepWiki):\n417\t  https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference\n418\t- sqlite-vec metadata + partition release:\n419\t  https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html\n420\t- Kyle Howells binary-quant benchmark:\n421\t  https://ikyle.me/blog/2025/binary-quantized-embeddings\n422\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d9c2010-470a-469e-a899-a4db3c31910c","uuid":"425d17b9-a9ee-4fef-a936-eca9f7c95d6d","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:24:23.133Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md","content":"---\ntitle: ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant\ndate: 2026-05-27\ntarget_release: 0.7.0\ndesc: Binary quantization (bit[768]) plus f32 rerank on the existing sqlite-vec extension, with metadata + partition_key schema migration, as the data-encoding change that closes AC-013 within the proposed 80 / 300 ms latency envelope. AC-019 keeps its existing 10× bound and is collaterally re-measured under the new query path. Architectural-lever accounting reaffirmed: PCACHE2 remains the 0.7.0 architectural lever; this is a data-encoding change.\nblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323 (read_search_in_tx hot SQL; Pack 2 rewrite); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846 (_fathomdb_vector_rows writer insert; Pack 1 double-write); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3278-3283 (vector_default CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE; Pack 1 schema migration); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107 (register_sqlite_vec_extension; unchanged but inspected); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260 (_fathomdb_embedder_profiles; UNCHANGED — embedder contract preserved); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2174,2242 (writer-loop pins; unchanged); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150 (AC013_BUDGET_P50/P99 re-pin in Pack 2); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:487 (ac_013_vector_retrieval_latency); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:609 (ac_019_mixed_retrieval_stress_workload_tail); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs new ac_NNN_recall_at_10 test (Pack 2); src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml:18 (sqlite-vec pin; stays =0.1.7); dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md (numeric lock-flip target, post Pack 2); dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md (post-0.7.0 ANN follow-ups)\nstatus: draft, HITL-required\n---\n\n# ADR-0.7.0 — Vector binary quantization (Pack 1 + Pack 2)\n\n**Status:** draft, HITL-required.\n\nThis ADR records the data-encoding decision that closes AC-013\nwithin the proposed 80 / 300 ms envelope in 0.7.0. AC-019 is\ncollaterally re-measured under the new query path — its existing\n10× stress-bound is expected to improve proportionally but its\nbudget shape is unchanged and its numeric row in the budgets ADR\nremains a placeholder pending the post-Pack-2 canonical-CI run\n(see § 6). It is paired with — and feeds into — the numeric\nlock-flip that will be made post-Pack-2 against\n`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`. That ADR\nremains the budget owner; this ADR commits the architectural shape\nthat makes those budgets reachable.\n\n## 1. Problem\n\nCanonical-CI measurement on 2026-05-27 under the locked\nW4.1-stacked-O1 (`L-Y1+L-Y2+L-B5+L-B4+L-D1-pcache2-O1`) stack\n(`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`)\nreports AC-013 at **p50 = 2048 ms, p99 = 2327 ms** on the\nN = 1,000,000 / dim 768 f32 fixture seeded by `VaryingEmbedder`\n(`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:296` and\n`:317`). AC-019 stress p99 = 8388 ms under bound 20964 ms; the\nbound is met today but the underlying per-query cost is the same\nhot path.\n\nThe proposed budgets in\n`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md` are\n**80 ms p50 / 300 ms p99**. The measurement is therefore\n**~25–40× over** the budget envelope. The current\n`AC013_BUDGET_P50 = 50ms` / `AC013_BUDGET_P99 = 200ms` constants in\n`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150` are\nthe unindexed-path-pre-lock values; the revised budgets ADR drafts\n80 / 300 ms but they have not yet been pinned in the test, by\ndesign (the re-pin is itself the Pack 2 RED gate).\n\n**Root cause.** The hot SQL at\n`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323`\n\n```\nSELECT rowid FROM vector_default\nWHERE embedding MATCH vec_f32(?1)\nORDER BY distance\nLIMIT 10\n```\n\ndrives a per-query O(N) brute-force scan over the\n`vector_default` vec0 table declared at\n`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3278-3283` as\n`USING vec0(embedding float[<dim>])` — i.e. a single global f32\ntable with no metadata columns, no partition keys, no auxiliary\nindex. At N = 1 M × dim 768 × 4 B that is 3.0 GB of memory\nstreamed per query; the observed 2048 ms p50 corresponds to\n~1.5 GB/s, which sits at the single-thread memory-read ceiling\non the canonical AMD EPYC 7763 runner. No SQLite engine knob can\nmove this — the bytes-per-row × rows-per-query product is the\nfloor. To close the gate we must either shrink the bytes per row,\nshrink the row count visited per query, or both.\n\nCross-reference: `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`\n§ \"Problem restated\" through § \"Tier 1 combined estimate\" enumerates\nthe lever surface; the present ADR commits to the Tier-1 #4 +\nTier-1 #1/#2 bundle as the load-bearing decision.\n\n## 2. Decision\n\nAdopt the following, to ship in two packs within the 0.7.0 release\nline (Pack 1 then Pack 2; pack boundary is for review granularity,\nnot release-boundary):\n\n1. **Binary quantization** of the f32 embedding into a sibling\n   `bit[768]` column on the existing `vector_default` vec0 table\n   (Pack 1.1 default per\n   `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`\n   § 1.1). The bit column is computed via sqlite-vec's\n   `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)` and written inside the same\n   writer transaction as the existing f32 insert. Sibling-table\n   fallback (`vector_default_bin`) is selected only if the\n   sibling-column shape hits the vec0 metadata column limit\n   (16 cols). The f32 `embedding` column is **retained** for\n   the rerank phase and for the recall-floor ground-truth pass —\n   it has two jobs after Pack 1.\n\n2. **Two-phase query** (Pack 2): bit-KNN top-K=64 candidates →\n   f32 rerank → top-10. The exact SQL shape (subject to the\n   sqlite-vec syntax confirmation called out in\n   `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § 2.2)\n   replaces the single-phase scan at\n   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323`. K is\n   a named constant / config knob so future tuning is cheap; the\n   K = 64 default is taken from the Kyle Howells and Cohere\n   binary-quant benches cited in\n   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #4.\n\n3. **Schema extension shipped on the same migration** (Pack 1):\n   - `source_type TEXT` as a vec0 **partition_key**\n     (HITL-locked 2026-05-27 in\n     `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`; cardinality ~6:\n     email, article, paper, meeting, note, todo). Maps from the\n     existing chunk-record vector kind at write time\n     (deterministic 1:1 mapping for the current single-kind\n     fixture; `source_type` is the authoritative going-forward\n     vocabulary).\n   - Additional metadata columns (`kind`, `created_at`, `tags`,\n     `project_mentions`, …) populated from the existing chunk\n     record. Per HITL Q5 in\n     `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` and\n     `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` Tier 1 #1,\n     descriptive retrieval filters live in metadata columns +\n     WHERE predicates, not in partition keys. The vec0 limit is\n     16 metadata columns; the Pack 1 schema MUST budget headroom.\n\n4. **Recall floor: ≥ 0.90 recall@10** vs f32 brute-force ground\n   truth on the AC-013 fixture\n   (`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`,\n   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § HITL responses #1).\n   Enforced by a new perf-gates test (`ac_NNN_recall_at_10`)\n   landed RED in Pack 2 before the query rewrite. Ground truth\n   is computed at test-setup via a one-pass brute-force scan\n   through the retained f32 column — single corpus, two jobs.\n\n5. **sqlite-vec pin stays `=0.1.7`**\n   (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml:18`). 0.1.7\n   already ships `bit[N]` and `vec_quantize_binary` per the\n   sqlite-vec release notes\n   (`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` Tier 1 #4\n   citation). Bump to `=0.1.9` is allowed in Pack 1 **only if\n   needed** for constraint-column refinements; not required and\n   not recommended without justification.\n\n6. **Embedder unchanged.** The `EmbedderIdentity` contract,\n   `VaryingEmbedder`, and the profile-pinning logic at\n   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260` are\n   not touched. HITL Q2 in\n   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § HITL responses\n   locked: KEEP existing embedder. Tier-1 #3 (smaller\n   embeddings) and Tier-1 #5 (matryoshka) are out of scope\n   for 0.7.0.\n\n7. **Single-writer + projection-cursor contracts preserved.**\n   Both column inserts commit in the same writer transaction at\n   the `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near\n   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846`. The\n   writer-loop pins at `:2174` and `:2242` are not touched.\n   AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 behavior is preserved.\n\n## 3. Alternatives considered (and rejected)\n\nEach alternative below was considered against the AC-013 gap; the\nresearch doc carries the long-form analysis.\n\n- **Vectorlite (HNSW SQLite extension).** Mechanism: load a\n  separate `USING vectorlite(...)` virtual table backed by an\n  HNSW graph stored in shadow tables. Rejected because the\n  upstream has had no release since 2024-08-19, has no\n  published 1 M × 768 benchmark, and counts as a structural\n  architectural lever stacked on top of PCACHE2 — violates the\n  one-architectural-lever-per-release rule. Cited:\n  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 2.\n\n- **sqlite-vec ANN alpha (v0.1.10-alpha.1).** Mechanism: use\n  the upstream-experimental ANN indices (`rescore`, `ivf`,\n  `DiskANN`). Rejected because the release is alpha-tagged and\n  upstream classifies it as not production-ready. Cited:\n  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3,\n  sqlite-vec releases.\n\n- **Rust-side `usearch` / `instant-distance`.** Mechanism:\n  pull KNN out of SQLite into a Rust-side ANN library and\n  rebuild the search verb around it. Rejected because the\n  blast radius (leaving SQLite for the KNN step, snapshot /\n  freshness handshake redesign, AC-017 cursor-freshness\n  re-derivation) is far larger than two packs of in-place\n  schema + query work, and the data-encoding lever closes the\n  gap without it. Cited:\n  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3 (integration\n  shape C).\n\n- **Embedder swap (dim reduction 768 → 384 or 256).**\n  Mechanism: replace `VaryingEmbedder` with a smaller embedder\n  to shrink bytes-per-row. Rejected by HITL Q2 lock 2026-05-27:\n  keep existing embedder. Rationale: switching embedders\n  requires a profile rotation through\n  `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles` and a corpus rebuild\n  (writer-cooperation cost), and even at dim 128 the\n  arithmetic-only saving is ~6× — well short of the ~25–40×\n  gap. Cited:\n  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #3,\n  § HITL responses.\n\n- **Partitioning alone (metadata prefilter / partition_key\n  without quantization).** Mechanism: keep the f32 column,\n  add `source_type` partition_key + metadata columns, push\n  filters into the WHERE clause. Rejected as load-bearing:\n  the AC-013 fixture is single-kind, so partitioning yields\n  zero benefit at the gate. Partitioning is **kept** as a\n  bundled deliverable in Pack 1 because it is the correct\n  shape for real workloads and avoids a second migration in\n  0.7.1 — but it does not close the gate on its own. Cited:\n  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #1, #2.\n\n## 4. Consequences\n\n- **Schema change (Pack 1).** `vector_default` gains the\n  `embedding_bin bit[768]` column, the `source_type` vec0\n  partition_key, and additional metadata columns (within the\n  vec0 16-column budget). Migration is a one-pass\n  `INSERT … SELECT vec_quantize_binary(embedding) FROM\n  vector_default` populating the bit column for the existing\n  corpus. Migration cost: ~3 GB read + ~96 MB write on the\n  1 M-row test corpus; ~64 s on the dev box per the handoff\n  estimate, well under the workflow timeout.\n\n- **Ingest cost (Pack 1).** The writer at the\n  `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near\n  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846` performs\n  a single additional `vec_quantize_binary()` and one extra\n  column write per row inside the same writer transaction.\n  No new commit; no new lock; no new SQLite handle. The\n  single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contract is\n  preserved bit-for-bit. Storage grows by ~3 % (96 B per row\n  on top of the 3072 B f32 footprint).\n\n- **Query-path rewrite (Pack 2).** Replace\n  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323` with\n  the two-phase shape outlined in\n  `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § 2.2.\n  No change to the writer side, no change to the projection-\n  cursor handshake, no change to `register_sqlite_vec_extension`\n  at `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107`. K = 64\n  is named as a constant for future tuning.\n\n- **Recall floor enforced as a RED test.** A new perf-gates\n  test (e.g. `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`) computes brute-force f32\n  ground truth at test-setup against the retained f32 column,\n  runs the production search path, and asserts\n  `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` on the AC-013 fixture. Lands RED in\n  Pack 2.1 alongside the latency budget re-pin\n  (`tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150` → 80 / 300 ms) and must\n  remain RED at canonical-CI N = 1 M scale until Pack 2.2's\n  query rewrite lands. Both gates GREEN at canonical-CI is\n  the Pack 2 close criterion.\n\n- **AC-019 carry.** The existing 10× bound on AC-019 stays\n  unchanged; the same two-phase query shape benefits AC-019\n  proportionally. AC-019 is expected to improve substantially\n  but no new bound is pinned here.\n\n- **AC-012 / AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 unchanged.** The\n  writer-loop pins (`:2174`, `:2242`), the embedder profile\n  table, and the reader-pool concurrency surface are all\n  untouched. Pack 1 changes schema but not query semantics, so\n  these tests stay GREEN through both packs.\n\n- **Post-0.7.0 follow-ups.** Graph-index ANN (vectorlite,\n  sqlite-vec ANN alpha, Rust-side `usearch`) and\n  matryoshka / smaller-embedder work are tracked in\n  `dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md` for 0.7.1+ if real-workload\n  telemetry shows the binary-quant scan is insufficient.\n\n## 5. Architectural-lever accounting\n\nThe 0.7.0 architectural lever is **`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2`**, locked\nby `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md`. The decision\nin § 2 of this ADR is a **data-encoding change** (schema +\nquantization function + two-phase SQL), not a second architectural\nlever:\n\n- It does not change the SQLite build, the SQLite vendor, the WAL\n  format, or the page-cache allocator.\n- It does not change the reader-pool topology, the writer-lock\n  shape, the projection-cursor contract, or the snapshot-freshness\n  contract.\n- It does not change the embedder identity or the profile-pinning\n  protocol.\n- It changes only the bytes stored per row in the vec0 table and\n  the SQL the reader emits against it.\n\nThis disposition is reaffirmed verbatim from\n`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § \"Architectural-lever\naccounting\". The HITL doc records the same call.\n\n**Fallback.** If a future reviewer (codex or HITL) counts\nbinary-quant + rerank as a second architectural lever stacked on\nPCACHE2, the agreed fallback per the handoff and the research doc\nis to ship **Pack 1 only in 0.7.0** (schema migration + ingest\ndouble-write; no reader behavior change; AC-013 stays at\n2048 / 2327 ms) and slip **Pack 2 to 0.7.1** (query rewrite + RED\ntests + lock-flip). The Pack 1-only shape preserves the on-disk\nshape for the future Pack 2 cutover and avoids a second migration.\nEscalation trigger is called out in\n`dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § \"Open\nitems the implementing agent should escalate to HITL\".\n\n## 6. Open questions / HITL gates\n\n- **Final numeric AC-013 / AC-019 budgets.** The 80 / 300 ms\n  numbers in § 1 are the proposed envelope from\n  `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`; the\n  final pinned values land after the P2-CANONICAL run, HITL\n  signs the numeric budgets, and the lock-flip is applied to the\n  budgets ADR. The Pack 2 perf-gates re-pin\n  (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`)\n  uses 80 / 300 ms initially; HITL may tighten by ~10 % headroom\n  against the measured numbers at lock time.\n\n- **K-value selection.** Default K = 64 from the binary-quant\n  literature. If the recall-floor test falls below 0.90 at K = 64\n  on canonical-CI scale, escalate before Pack 2 GREEN-test commit\n  (per `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`\n  § \"Open items\"). K may need to rise to 128 or 256; the choice\n  is documented in the closing slice JSON and reflected in the\n  named constant.\n\n- **vec0 metadata column budget.** The vec0 16-column cap\n  constrains the Pack 1 schema. If the desired metadata schema\n  (including future fields for the corpus / API work tracked\n  separately) cannot fit alongside the partition_key + bit\n  column, escalate before Pack 1 schema design freezes. Fallback\n  is the sibling-table shape (`vector_default_bin`) called out\n  in § 2 / Pack 1.1.\n\n- **`vec_quantize_binary()` input expectations.** `VaryingEmbedder`\n  produces L2-normalised f32 vectors\n  (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:322-326`),\n  and the research note records the same\n  (`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md:164-165`). Binary\n  quantization via `vec_quantize_binary()` is a sign-pattern\n  transform that is invariant to positive scaling, so L2 norm\n  itself is not load-bearing, but the function's exact input\n  contract (signed-zero handling, NaN behaviour) has not been\n  validated against `VaryingEmbedder` output. If sqlite-vec 0.1.7's\n  `vec_quantize_binary()` rejects the f32 blobs produced by the\n  current writer path or returns degenerate bit patterns, escalate\n  before Pack 1 ingest changes land (per the handoff § \"Open\n  items\"). The fixture concentrates mass on 6 of 768 coordinates\n  (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:317`),\n  which is atypically friendly to sign-pattern quantisation —\n  HITL is owed the note that AC-013's recall headroom may\n  overstate real-workload headroom.\n\n## 7. Status / next actions\n\n- **Status: `draft, HITL-required`.** No lock-flip happens in this\n  ADR until canonical-CI is GREEN at the re-pinned budgets and\n  the recall floor and HITL signs the numeric budgets in\n  `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`.\n\n- **Immediate next slice.** Orchestrator spawns a codex reviewer\n  on this ADR draft, then promotes the verdict per\n  `dev/design/orchestration.md` § 4. If review is PASS, Pack 1\n  schema-migration + ingest-double-write slice is next.\n\n- **Lock-flip sequencing.** Per the handoff § \"Done = ?\", this\n  ADR moves to `status: locked` only after: Pack 1 lands;\n  Pack 2 lands; canonical-CI dispatch shows AC-013 GREEN at the\n  re-pinned 80 / 300 ms (or HITL-revised) budgets; the new\n  recall-floor test is GREEN at ≥ 0.90; AC-019 verdict is\n  re-measured under the new query path; HITL signs off on the\n  numeric budgets in the revised-budgets ADR. Lock-flip is\n  orchestrator's; this draft does not flip prematurely.\n\n## Citations\n\n- `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`\n  (this ADR's mandating handoff; § Step 0 enumerates the\n  must-cover items).\n- `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` (HITL-RESPONDED;\n  Tier 1 / 2 / 3 catalogue; Pack 1 / 2 split locked).\n- `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` (HITL decision\n  record: recall floor 0.90 @ k=10; `source_type` partition_key;\n  cardinality ~6; sqlite-vec 0.1.7).\n- `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md` (PCACHE2 is\n  the 0.7.0 architectural lever; pattern reference for this\n  ADR's structure).\n- `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`\n  (numeric budget owner; lock-flip target post-Pack-2).\n- `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`\n  (canonical-CI measurement: p50 = 2048 ms, p99 = 2327 ms at\n  N = 1 M, W4.1-stacked-O1 stack, 2026-05-27).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323` (hot\n  SQL; Pack 2 rewrite site).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846`\n  (`_fathomdb_vector_rows` writer insert; Pack 1 double-write\n  site).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3278-3283`\n  (`vector_default` CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE; Pack 1 schema\n  migration site).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107`\n  (`register_sqlite_vec_extension`; inspected, unchanged).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260`\n  (`_fathomdb_embedder_profiles`; UNCHANGED — embedder identity\n  contract preserved).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`\n  (`AC013_BUDGET_P50` / `AC013_BUDGET_P99`; Pack 2 re-pin\n  target).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:487`\n  (`ac_013_vector_retrieval_latency`).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:609`\n  (`ac_019_mixed_retrieval_stress_workload_tail`).\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml:18`\n  (`sqlite-vec = \"=0.1.7\"`).\n- sqlite-vec binary quantization guide:\n  https://alexgarcia.xyz/sqlite-vec/guides/binary-quant.html\n- sqlite-vec API reference (DeepWiki):\n  https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference\n- sqlite-vec metadata + partition release:\n  https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html\n- Kyle Howells binary-quant benchmark:\n  https://ikyle.me/blog/2025/binary-quantized-embeddings\n","numLines":422,"startLine":1,"totalLines":422}}}
