{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FbSohmpagQ98KnokPTjMqA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# 0.7.0 — HITL Q1/Q2/Q4 decisions\n2\t\n3\tDrafted: 2026-05-26\n4\tUpdated: 2026-05-26 (HITL responses incorporated)\n5\tStatus: **HITL-RESPONDED, ready for ADR lock-flip pending AC-013/AC-019 canonical-CI numbers**\n6\t\n7\tThis doc consolidates the perf-experiments campaign data\n8\t(`dev/plans/0.7.0-perf-experiments.md` + the closure JSONs in\n9\t`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-*.json`) into the HITL decisions\n10\tfor 0.7.0.\n11\t\n12\tThe campaign closed with canonical-CI dispatches on the\n13\t`ubuntu-latest` perf-canonical workflow (4-core AMD EPYC 9V74 on\n14\tAzure-backed Ubuntu 24.04.4). Dev-box (24-core Threadripper PRO\n15\t5945WX) served as pre-screen.\n16\t\n17\t## Canonical-CI numbers (N=1 per cell, 1M corpus)\n18\t\n19\t| Configuration | AC-012 p50 | AC-012 p99 | AC-020 seq | AC-020 conc | AC-020 bound |\n20\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n21\t| W1.1 — baseline (no levers) | 162 | 526 | 177 | 65 | 33 |\n22\t| W5.3 — canonical-SQLite stack (no PCACHE2) | 66 | 221 | 166 | 54 | 31 |\n23\t| **W4.1-stacked-O1 — PCACHE2 stack (locked config)** | **57** | **135** | **176** | **56** | 33 |\n24\t| W4.1-ac013 — AC-013 on locked stack | AC-013 p50=**2048**, p99=**2327** (seed 562 s); AC-019 baseline_p99=**2096**, stress_p99=**8388**, bound=20964 ms (8 threads × 250 queries) | | | | |\n25\t\n26\t## HITL responses (locked)\n27\t\n28\t### Q1 — Revised budgets\n29\t\n30\t**AC-012: Option A — p50 ≤ 60 ms, p99 ≤ 150 ms** ✅ LOCKED\n31\t\n32\tMeasurement-pinned against canonical-CI 57/135 + ~5% headroom.\n33\tTightens the original draft (50/200) on p99, loosens on p50 to\n34\tmatch measurement.\n35\t\n36\t**AC-020: Option A in spirit, but expressed in absolute ms — NOT speedup ratio** ✅ LOCKED\n37\t\n38\tThe 5.33× ratio (`1.5 / 8`) framing assumed an 8-core canonical\n39\trunner; canonical CI is 4-core. The right expression is absolute\n40\tms envelopes that catch regressions independent of core count:\n41\t\n42\t- **Sequential ≤ 250 ms** at 1M corpus on canonical CI.\n43\t  (Measured 176 ms at W4.1-stacked-O1; 42% headroom.)\n44\t- **Concurrent ≤ 80 ms** at 1M corpus on canonical CI, 8\n45\t  reader threads.\n46\t  (Measured 56 ms at W4.1-stacked-O1; 43% headroom.)\n47\t\n48\tThe existing `1.5 / 8` ratio in `tests/perf_gates.rs:245` is\n49\t**replaced**, not preserved. The AC-020 RED-test asserts the two\n50\tabsolute bounds above instead.\n51\t\n52\tSource comment in the test should note: *\"absolute-ms envelope\n53\tpinned against the locked PCACHE2-stack canonical-CI measurement;\n54\tthe prior `concurrent ≤ sequential * 1.5/8` ratio was a proxy for\n55\t'cores should multiply throughput' that broke down on the 4-core\n56\tcanonical runner. If canonical CI moves to ≥8-core hardware,\n57\tre-measure and tighten.\"*\n58\t\n59\t**AC-013 / AC-019: not descoped — finish the work** ✅ LOCKED\n60\t\n61\tCanonical-CI N=1M dispatch under W4.1-stacked-O1 stack completed\n62\t2026-05-27 (workflow run 26482279276, ~169 min wall time):\n63\t\n64\t- AC-013 p50 = **2048 ms**, p99 = **2327 ms** (seed cost 562 s).\n65\t- AC-019 baseline_p99 = 2096 ms, stress_p99 = 8388 ms,\n66\t  bound = 20964 ms (10× baseline). **AC-019 passes** its\n67\t  bound expression (stress within 10× of baseline).\n68\t\n69\t**Major finding — AC-013 is 25–40× over the ADR-draft 80/300\n70\tbudget.** The bottleneck is per-query O(N) full-scan through the\n71\t`vec0` virtual table — no ANN index. At dim=768 × 1M rows, every\n72\tquery examines all 1M vectors. PCACHE2 / MEMSTATUS / pragmas\n73\tcannot move this — the bottleneck is the linear ANN scan, not\n74\tallocator / pcache contention.\n75\t\n76\t**HITL decision 2026-05-26: land a vector-retrieval cost fix\n77\tin 0.7.0.** Expands 0.7.0 scope from \"perf-only single-thrust\"\n78\tto \"perf + vector-cost\".\n79\t\n80\t**Research returned 2026-05-27** (`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`):"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d9c2010-470a-469e-a899-a4db3c31910c","uuid":"5a3f7daf-6cb1-427a-8eae-4165b6941d69","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:24:49.975Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md","content":"# 0.7.0 — HITL Q1/Q2/Q4 decisions\n\nDrafted: 2026-05-26\nUpdated: 2026-05-26 (HITL responses incorporated)\nStatus: **HITL-RESPONDED, ready for ADR lock-flip pending AC-013/AC-019 canonical-CI numbers**\n\nThis doc consolidates the perf-experiments campaign data\n(`dev/plans/0.7.0-perf-experiments.md` + the closure JSONs in\n`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-*.json`) into the HITL decisions\nfor 0.7.0.\n\nThe campaign closed with canonical-CI dispatches on the\n`ubuntu-latest` perf-canonical workflow (4-core AMD EPYC 9V74 on\nAzure-backed Ubuntu 24.04.4). Dev-box (24-core Threadripper PRO\n5945WX) served as pre-screen.\n\n## Canonical-CI numbers (N=1 per cell, 1M corpus)\n\n| Configuration | AC-012 p50 | AC-012 p99 | AC-020 seq | AC-020 conc | AC-020 bound |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| W1.1 — baseline (no levers) | 162 | 526 | 177 | 65 | 33 |\n| W5.3 — canonical-SQLite stack (no PCACHE2) | 66 | 221 | 166 | 54 | 31 |\n| **W4.1-stacked-O1 — PCACHE2 stack (locked config)** | **57** | **135** | **176** | **56** | 33 |\n| W4.1-ac013 — AC-013 on locked stack | AC-013 p50=**2048**, p99=**2327** (seed 562 s); AC-019 baseline_p99=**2096**, stress_p99=**8388**, bound=20964 ms (8 threads × 250 queries) | | | | |\n\n## HITL responses (locked)\n\n### Q1 — Revised budgets\n\n**AC-012: Option A — p50 ≤ 60 ms, p99 ≤ 150 ms** ✅ LOCKED\n\nMeasurement-pinned against canonical-CI 57/135 + ~5% headroom.\nTightens the original draft (50/200) on p99, loosens on p50 to\nmatch measurement.\n\n**AC-020: Option A in spirit, but expressed in absolute ms — NOT speedup ratio** ✅ LOCKED\n\nThe 5.33× ratio (`1.5 / 8`) framing assumed an 8-core canonical\nrunner; canonical CI is 4-core. The right expression is absolute\nms envelopes that catch regressions independent of core count:\n\n- **Sequential ≤ 250 ms** at 1M corpus on canonical CI.\n  (Measured 176 ms at W4.1-stacked-O1; 42% headroom.)\n- **Concurrent ≤ 80 ms** at 1M corpus on canonical CI, 8\n  reader threads.\n  (Measured 56 ms at W4.1-stacked-O1; 43% headroom.)\n\nThe existing `1.5 / 8` ratio in `tests/perf_gates.rs:245` is\n**replaced**, not preserved. The AC-020 RED-test asserts the two\nabsolute bounds above instead.\n\nSource comment in the test should note: *\"absolute-ms envelope\npinned against the locked PCACHE2-stack canonical-CI measurement;\nthe prior `concurrent ≤ sequential * 1.5/8` ratio was a proxy for\n'cores should multiply throughput' that broke down on the 4-core\ncanonical runner. If canonical CI moves to ≥8-core hardware,\nre-measure and tighten.\"*\n\n**AC-013 / AC-019: not descoped — finish the work** ✅ LOCKED\n\nCanonical-CI N=1M dispatch under W4.1-stacked-O1 stack completed\n2026-05-27 (workflow run 26482279276, ~169 min wall time):\n\n- AC-013 p50 = **2048 ms**, p99 = **2327 ms** (seed cost 562 s).\n- AC-019 baseline_p99 = 2096 ms, stress_p99 = 8388 ms,\n  bound = 20964 ms (10× baseline). **AC-019 passes** its\n  bound expression (stress within 10× of baseline).\n\n**Major finding — AC-013 is 25–40× over the ADR-draft 80/300\nbudget.** The bottleneck is per-query O(N) full-scan through the\n`vec0` virtual table — no ANN index. At dim=768 × 1M rows, every\nquery examines all 1M vectors. PCACHE2 / MEMSTATUS / pragmas\ncannot move this — the bottleneck is the linear ANN scan, not\nallocator / pcache contention.\n\n**HITL decision 2026-05-26: land a vector-retrieval cost fix\nin 0.7.0.** Expands 0.7.0 scope from \"perf-only single-thrust\"\nto \"perf + vector-cost\".\n\n**Research returned 2026-05-27** (`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`):","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":296}}}
