{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012XwetdufcwdpWGyy16uTVP","type":"tool_result","content":"85\tpursued in 0.7.0.\n86\t\n87\t**HITL responses (locked 2026-05-27):**\n88\t\n89\t1. **Recall floor**: ≥ 90 % recall@10 vs f32 ground truth on the\n90\t   AC-013 fixture (initial floor; tighten in later release).\n91\t2. **Embedder**: KEEP existing. Tier-1 #3 (smaller embeddings)\n92\t   and #5 (matryoshka) out of scope for 0.7.0.\n93\t3. **Metadata + partition_key schema**: YES, ship in 0.7.0 —\n94\t   bundled into Pack 1 of the implementation.\n95\t\n96\t**Implementation: 2 packs within 0.7.0.**\n97\t\n98\t- **Pack 1** — schema migration + ingest double-write. Adds\n99\t  `bit[768]` sibling column + metadata columns + partition_key\n100\t  to the vec0 schema; writer double-writes f32 + bit. No reader\n101\t  change yet; AC-013 stays pinned at the unindexed 2048/2327\n102\t  numbers. Correctness gate: migration round-trip test.\n103\t- **Pack 2** — query-path swap. `read_search_in_tx` becomes\n104\t  two-phase (bit KNN top-K → f32 rerank). Re-pins AC-013 to\n105\t  ≤ 80 / 300 ms and adds the recall-floor RED test\n106\t  (≥ 0.90 @ k=10).\n107\t\n108\tArchitectural-lever disposition: the binary-quant + rerank\n109\tquery shape is a **data-encoding change**, not a second\n110\tarchitectural lever (PCACHE2 already occupies that slot in\n111\t0.7.0). Both packs ship in 0.7.0. Fallback if a future reviewer\n112\tdisagrees on the lever counting: Pack 1 stays in 0.7.0;\n113\tPack 2 slips to 0.7.1.\n114\t\n115\tImplementation handoff: `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`.\n116\tAC-013 / AC-019 budgets in the revised-budgets ADR remain\n117\tplaceholders until Pack 2's canonical-CI measurement returns.\n118\t\n119\t### Test corpus (locked 2026-05-27)\n120\t\n121\tResearch at `dev/notes/0.7.0-test-corpus-research.md`. HITL\n122\tresponses:\n123\t\n124\t1. **Enron commit: OK** with the CMU April-2026 impersonation\n125\t   note on the corpus card.\n126\t2. **Synthetic cross-doc chain generator: in 0.7.0 scope** —\n127\t   needed to test the vector implementation; bundles with\n128\t   Pack 2.\n129\t3. **Recall floor 0.90 @ k=10**: current bar; revisit after\n130\t   empirical run.\n131\t4. **CI artifact**: cache the corpus in GitHub Actions cache.\n132\t   License-clean sources (CNN/DailyMail Apache-2.0, OpenAlex\n133\t   CC0, Enron) can additionally be committed; CC-BY-NC-SA\n134\t   sources (ELITR) live in cache only, fetched at cache miss.\n135\t5. **Partition_key: `source_type`** — locked. Supersedes the\n136\t   `kind` default in the Pack 1 handoff. Pack 1 schema MUST\n137\t   use `source_type` as the vec0 partition_key.\n138\t\n139\tDefault corpus version for Pack 2 RED tests: **Version B\n140\t(~10K docs)** per the research recommendation. Sources:\n141\tEnron / EnronQA (emails), QMSum + ELITR (meetings), PMC OA +\n142\tS2ORC + OpenAlex (academic), CNN/DailyMail (news), Imperative\n143\tTo-Do (todos), public daily-log repos + synthetic generator\n144\t(notes).\n145\t\n146\tCorpus-build handoff:\n147\t`dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-CORPUS-BUILD-HANDOFF.md`.\n148\t\n149\tThe PCACHE2 stack is still the right lock for AC-012 / AC-020;\n150\tthe ANN-index addition is **orthogonal** (different bottleneck,\n151\tdifferent code path). Lock-flip on the revised-budgets ADR for\n152\tAC-012 / AC-020 should NOT block on the ANN-index slice; AC-013\n153\tand AC-019 budget rows in that ADR are placeholders pending the\n154\tANN slice's measurement.\n155\t\n156\t**AC-071 (top-K LIMIT default): additive opt-in (default unlimited)** ✅ LOCKED\n157\t\n158\t### Q2 — AC-020 architectural lever\n159\t\n160\t**PCACHE2 (Option 1)** ✅ LOCKED\n161\t\n162\t#### Clarification on \"how PCACHE2 combines with other tested settings\"\n163\t\n164\tThe locked production stack is **W4.1-stacked-O1**, which is one\n165\tbundle of co-enabled knobs:\n166\t\n167\t| Knob | What it is | How it composes with PCACHE2 |\n168\t|---|---|---|\n169\t| `SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` | Custom page-cache implementation (`pcache2.rs`, ~360 LOC). Replaces SQLite's default `pcache1`. | **The lever.** Process-start FFI. |\n170\t| `SQLITE_CONFIG_MEMSTATUS=0` | Disables SQLite's allocator-statistics mutex. | **Stacks additively.** Independent contention surface from the pcache1 mutex; both gains compound. |\n171\t| `page_size=8192` (writer pragma) | Increases SQLite B-tree page size from default 4K to 8K. | **Stacks additively.** Halves the number of pcache fetches per query; multiplies PCACHE2's per-fetch savings. |\n172\t| Reader pragmas: `cache_size=-262144`, `mmap_size=268435456`, `temp_store=MEMORY`, `synchronous=NORMAL` | Standard SQLite tuning: 256 MB cache cap, 256 MB mmap, in-memory temp tables, single-writer durability. | **Stacks additively.** Increases pcache hit rate (so PCACHE2's fast path runs more often) and reduces I/O sync overhead. |\n173\t| `SQLITE_CONFIG_PAGECACHE 1GB pre-alloc` | Pre-allocates 1 GB of pcache1 backing memory at process start. | **MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE with PCACHE2.** PCACHE2 replaces the entire pcache subsystem; PAGECACHE has no effect when PCACHE2 is installed. The prototype omits PAGECACHE under PCACHE2; the production graduation should make this explicit (refuse to install both, or document that PAGECACHE is silently ignored). |\n174\t| `HashSet<key>` (unpinned eviction candidates inside PCACHE2) | Internal data structure for O(1) eviction lookup. | **Implementation detail of PCACHE2, not a separate lever.** The prototype uses a `HashSet` (best-effort eviction); production graduation should consider a doubly-linked-list LRU for better eviction quality under cache pressure. The AC-020 / AC-012 gates do not exercise tight cache pressure so the prototype suffices for the contract. |\n175\t| `LIMIT k=1000` (AC-012 query shape, Q4 lever) | Caps result-set size on the search verb. | **Independent of PCACHE2.** Helps AC-012 by reducing rows materialised; orthogonal to allocator/pcache contention. Recommended as opt-in per Q4 / AC-071 above. |\n176\t\n177\t**HITL also decided 2026-05-26: stay with W4.1-stacked-O1 as the\n178\tlocked 0.7.0 stack; do NOT pursue proper-LRU or `page_size=16384`\n179\t(alone or combined) in 0.7.0.** Rationale captured in\n180\t`dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md`: locked stack lands GREEN with\n181\tmaterial headroom; the measured 16K-solo prior (W4.0g) regressed\n182\ton AC-020; the LRU benefit is invisible on the AC fixtures and\n183\tneeds production-workload telemetry to size honestly. Both\n184\tvariations are eligible for a `0.8.0-PERF-PCACHE2-PRODUCTION`\n185\tslice keyed on the trigger conditions in the followups note.\n186\t\n187\t**Action items for the PCACHE2 production-graduation slice\n188\t(`0.7.0-PERF-PCACHE2`):**\n189\t\n190\t1. Replace `FATHOMDB_PERF_SQLITE_PCACHE2=1` env gate with a\n191\t   runtime-config field on `EngineRuntime::open` (whitepaper §13\n192\t   lookaside-config pattern).\n193\t2. Co-enable the full W4.1-stacked-O1 stack in `init_perf_*` /\n194\t   the corresponding production paths: MEMSTATUS_OFF + page_size=8192\n195\t   writer pragma + the four reader pragmas. These should be the\n196\t   default, not opt-in, under the locked release.\n197\t3. Ensure `SQLITE_CONFIG_PAGECACHE` is not also installed (it has\n198\t   no effect under PCACHE2 but the unused env var should be\n199\t   removed from the production path to avoid confusion).\n200\t4. Consider replacing PCACHE2's internal `HashSet` eviction with\n201\t   a proper LRU. Not required for the AC gates; required only\n202\t   under tight cache-pressure workloads. Land as a follow-up,\n203\t   noted in `dev/notes/performance-whitepaper-notes.md` §13.\n204\t5. Pin the AC-020 RED-test bounds to the absolute-ms envelopes\n205\t   above (per Q1 AC-020 lock).\n206\t6. Pin the AC-012 RED-test budgets to 60/150 (per Q1 AC-012 lock).\n207\t\n208\t#### Other levers tested but not part of the locked stack\n209\t\n210\t| Lever ID | What it is | Result | Status |\n211\t|---|---|---|---|\n212\t| L-A0 baseline | No experiment env vars | Floor (W1.1) | Reference only |\n213\t| L-B4 reader synchronous=NORMAL | Component of reader pragmas | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n214\t| L-B5 reader cache+mmap+temp pragmas | Component of reader pragmas | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n215\t| L-Y1 MEMSTATUS=0 | Disable allocator stats | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n216\t| L-Y2 page_size=8192 | Writer page size | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n217\t| L-Y3 SQLITE_CONFIG_PAGECACHE pre-alloc | Pre-allocated pcache1 backing | Superseded by PCACHE2 | Not in locked stack |\n218\t| **L-D1 PCACHE2** | Custom xCreate/xFetch/xUnpin | Closes both gates | **Locked** |\n219\t| L-C1 LIMIT k=1000 | Search-shape lever | Independent; AC-071 additive | Opt-in (Q4) |\n220\t| L-D2 WAL2 | WAL2 patchset | **OUT OF SCOPE** per HITL | Rejected |\n221\t| L-D3 R-W split | Reader/writer pool separation | **OUT OF SCOPE** per HITL | Rejected |\n222\t| L-D4 libSQL / sqlite3mc swap | Vendor-SQLite swap | **OUT OF SCOPE** per HITL | Rejected |\n223\t\n224\t`ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md` records WAL2 / R-W split\n225\t/ libSQL as rejected alternatives at lock-flip time.\n226\t\n227\t### Q4 — Top-K LIMIT shape\n228\t\n229\t**Additive opt-in (default unlimited; opt-in `--top-k` cap)** ✅ LOCKED\n230\t\n231\tPer the W4.1-stacked-O1 measurement, AC-012 closes on canonical\n232\tCI without any LIMIT changes (the `SEARCH_LIMIT=1000` env was\n233\tset during the dispatch but AC-012's measurement protocol uses\n234\tthe default-shape behavior — no cap applied). The LIMIT cap is a\n235\tknob for callers that want bounded latency, not a 0.7.0\n236\tbudget-closure dependency.\n237\t\n238\t## ADR lock-flip plan\n239\t\n240\tOnce the AC-013/AC-019 canonical-CI run completes:\n241\t\n242\t1. Update `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`:\n243\t   - `status: draft` → `status: locked`\n244\t   - AC-012 budget: `p50 ≤ 50 ms; p99 ≤ 200 ms` → `p50 ≤ 60 ms; p99 ≤ 150 ms`"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d9c2010-470a-469e-a899-a4db3c31910c","uuid":"b4f00764-e259-4b7a-9ca0-84c076c53038","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:24:57.116Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md","content":"pursued in 0.7.0.\n\n**HITL responses (locked 2026-05-27):**\n\n1. **Recall floor**: ≥ 90 % recall@10 vs f32 ground truth on the\n   AC-013 fixture (initial floor; tighten in later release).\n2. **Embedder**: KEEP existing. Tier-1 #3 (smaller embeddings)\n   and #5 (matryoshka) out of scope for 0.7.0.\n3. **Metadata + partition_key schema**: YES, ship in 0.7.0 —\n   bundled into Pack 1 of the implementation.\n\n**Implementation: 2 packs within 0.7.0.**\n\n- **Pack 1** — schema migration + ingest double-write. Adds\n  `bit[768]` sibling column + metadata columns + partition_key\n  to the vec0 schema; writer double-writes f32 + bit. No reader\n  change yet; AC-013 stays pinned at the unindexed 2048/2327\n  numbers. Correctness gate: migration round-trip test.\n- **Pack 2** — query-path swap. `read_search_in_tx` becomes\n  two-phase (bit KNN top-K → f32 rerank). Re-pins AC-013 to\n  ≤ 80 / 300 ms and adds the recall-floor RED test\n  (≥ 0.90 @ k=10).\n\nArchitectural-lever disposition: the binary-quant + rerank\nquery shape is a **data-encoding change**, not a second\narchitectural lever (PCACHE2 already occupies that slot in\n0.7.0). Both packs ship in 0.7.0. Fallback if a future reviewer\ndisagrees on the lever counting: Pack 1 stays in 0.7.0;\nPack 2 slips to 0.7.1.\n\nImplementation handoff: `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`.\nAC-013 / AC-019 budgets in the revised-budgets ADR remain\nplaceholders until Pack 2's canonical-CI measurement returns.\n\n### Test corpus (locked 2026-05-27)\n\nResearch at `dev/notes/0.7.0-test-corpus-research.md`. HITL\nresponses:\n\n1. **Enron commit: OK** with the CMU April-2026 impersonation\n   note on the corpus card.\n2. **Synthetic cross-doc chain generator: in 0.7.0 scope** —\n   needed to test the vector implementation; bundles with\n   Pack 2.\n3. **Recall floor 0.90 @ k=10**: current bar; revisit after\n   empirical run.\n4. **CI artifact**: cache the corpus in GitHub Actions cache.\n   License-clean sources (CNN/DailyMail Apache-2.0, OpenAlex\n   CC0, Enron) can additionally be committed; CC-BY-NC-SA\n   sources (ELITR) live in cache only, fetched at cache miss.\n5. **Partition_key: `source_type`** — locked. Supersedes the\n   `kind` default in the Pack 1 handoff. Pack 1 schema MUST\n   use `source_type` as the vec0 partition_key.\n\nDefault corpus version for Pack 2 RED tests: **Version B\n(~10K docs)** per the research recommendation. Sources:\nEnron / EnronQA (emails), QMSum + ELITR (meetings), PMC OA +\nS2ORC + OpenAlex (academic), CNN/DailyMail (news), Imperative\nTo-Do (todos), public daily-log repos + synthetic generator\n(notes).\n\nCorpus-build handoff:\n`dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-CORPUS-BUILD-HANDOFF.md`.\n\nThe PCACHE2 stack is still the right lock for AC-012 / AC-020;\nthe ANN-index addition is **orthogonal** (different bottleneck,\ndifferent code path). Lock-flip on the revised-budgets ADR for\nAC-012 / AC-020 should NOT block on the ANN-index slice; AC-013\nand AC-019 budget rows in that ADR are placeholders pending the\nANN slice's measurement.\n\n**AC-071 (top-K LIMIT default): additive opt-in (default unlimited)** ✅ LOCKED\n\n### Q2 — AC-020 architectural lever\n\n**PCACHE2 (Option 1)** ✅ LOCKED\n\n#### Clarification on \"how PCACHE2 combines with other tested settings\"\n\nThe locked production stack is **W4.1-stacked-O1**, which is one\nbundle of co-enabled knobs:\n\n| Knob | What it is | How it composes with PCACHE2 |\n|---|---|---|\n| `SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` | Custom page-cache implementation (`pcache2.rs`, ~360 LOC). Replaces SQLite's default `pcache1`. | **The lever.** Process-start FFI. |\n| `SQLITE_CONFIG_MEMSTATUS=0` | Disables SQLite's allocator-statistics mutex. | **Stacks additively.** Independent contention surface from the pcache1 mutex; both gains compound. |\n| `page_size=8192` (writer pragma) | Increases SQLite B-tree page size from default 4K to 8K. | **Stacks additively.** Halves the number of pcache fetches per query; multiplies PCACHE2's per-fetch savings. |\n| Reader pragmas: `cache_size=-262144`, `mmap_size=268435456`, `temp_store=MEMORY`, `synchronous=NORMAL` | Standard SQLite tuning: 256 MB cache cap, 256 MB mmap, in-memory temp tables, single-writer durability. | **Stacks additively.** Increases pcache hit rate (so PCACHE2's fast path runs more often) and reduces I/O sync overhead. |\n| `SQLITE_CONFIG_PAGECACHE 1GB pre-alloc` | Pre-allocates 1 GB of pcache1 backing memory at process start. | **MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE with PCACHE2.** PCACHE2 replaces the entire pcache subsystem; PAGECACHE has no effect when PCACHE2 is installed. The prototype omits PAGECACHE under PCACHE2; the production graduation should make this explicit (refuse to install both, or document that PAGECACHE is silently ignored). |\n| `HashSet<key>` (unpinned eviction candidates inside PCACHE2) | Internal data structure for O(1) eviction lookup. | **Implementation detail of PCACHE2, not a separate lever.** The prototype uses a `HashSet` (best-effort eviction); production graduation should consider a doubly-linked-list LRU for better eviction quality under cache pressure. The AC-020 / AC-012 gates do not exercise tight cache pressure so the prototype suffices for the contract. |\n| `LIMIT k=1000` (AC-012 query shape, Q4 lever) | Caps result-set size on the search verb. | **Independent of PCACHE2.** Helps AC-012 by reducing rows materialised; orthogonal to allocator/pcache contention. Recommended as opt-in per Q4 / AC-071 above. |\n\n**HITL also decided 2026-05-26: stay with W4.1-stacked-O1 as the\nlocked 0.7.0 stack; do NOT pursue proper-LRU or `page_size=16384`\n(alone or combined) in 0.7.0.** Rationale captured in\n`dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md`: locked stack lands GREEN with\nmaterial headroom; the measured 16K-solo prior (W4.0g) regressed\non AC-020; the LRU benefit is invisible on the AC fixtures and\nneeds production-workload telemetry to size honestly. Both\nvariations are eligible for a `0.8.0-PERF-PCACHE2-PRODUCTION`\nslice keyed on the trigger conditions in the followups note.\n\n**Action items for the PCACHE2 production-graduation slice\n(`0.7.0-PERF-PCACHE2`):**\n\n1. Replace `FATHOMDB_PERF_SQLITE_PCACHE2=1` env gate with a\n   runtime-config field on `EngineRuntime::open` (whitepaper §13\n   lookaside-config pattern).\n2. Co-enable the full W4.1-stacked-O1 stack in `init_perf_*` /\n   the corresponding production paths: MEMSTATUS_OFF + page_size=8192\n   writer pragma + the four reader pragmas. These should be the\n   default, not opt-in, under the locked release.\n3. Ensure `SQLITE_CONFIG_PAGECACHE` is not also installed (it has\n   no effect under PCACHE2 but the unused env var should be\n   removed from the production path to avoid confusion).\n4. Consider replacing PCACHE2's internal `HashSet` eviction with\n   a proper LRU. Not required for the AC gates; required only\n   under tight cache-pressure workloads. Land as a follow-up,\n   noted in `dev/notes/performance-whitepaper-notes.md` §13.\n5. Pin the AC-020 RED-test bounds to the absolute-ms envelopes\n   above (per Q1 AC-020 lock).\n6. Pin the AC-012 RED-test budgets to 60/150 (per Q1 AC-012 lock).\n\n#### Other levers tested but not part of the locked stack\n\n| Lever ID | What it is | Result | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| L-A0 baseline | No experiment env vars | Floor (W1.1) | Reference only |\n| L-B4 reader synchronous=NORMAL | Component of reader pragmas | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n| L-B5 reader cache+mmap+temp pragmas | Component of reader pragmas | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n| L-Y1 MEMSTATUS=0 | Disable allocator stats | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n| L-Y2 page_size=8192 | Writer page size | Stacked into W4.1-stacked-O1 | Locked |\n| L-Y3 SQLITE_CONFIG_PAGECACHE pre-alloc | Pre-allocated pcache1 backing | Superseded by PCACHE2 | Not in locked stack |\n| **L-D1 PCACHE2** | Custom xCreate/xFetch/xUnpin | Closes both gates | **Locked** |\n| L-C1 LIMIT k=1000 | Search-shape lever | Independent; AC-071 additive | Opt-in (Q4) |\n| L-D2 WAL2 | WAL2 patchset | **OUT OF SCOPE** per HITL | Rejected |\n| L-D3 R-W split | Reader/writer pool separation | **OUT OF SCOPE** per HITL | Rejected |\n| L-D4 libSQL / sqlite3mc swap | Vendor-SQLite swap | **OUT OF SCOPE** per HITL | Rejected |\n\n`ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md` records WAL2 / R-W split\n/ libSQL as rejected alternatives at lock-flip time.\n\n### Q4 — Top-K LIMIT shape\n\n**Additive opt-in (default unlimited; opt-in `--top-k` cap)** ✅ LOCKED\n\nPer the W4.1-stacked-O1 measurement, AC-012 closes on canonical\nCI without any LIMIT changes (the `SEARCH_LIMIT=1000` env was\nset during the dispatch but AC-012's measurement protocol uses\nthe default-shape behavior — no cap applied). The LIMIT cap is a\nknob for callers that want bounded latency, not a 0.7.0\nbudget-closure dependency.\n\n## ADR lock-flip plan\n\nOnce the AC-013/AC-019 canonical-CI run completes:\n\n1. Update `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`:\n   - `status: draft` → `status: locked`\n   - AC-012 budget: `p50 ≤ 50 ms; p99 ≤ 200 ms` → `p50 ≤ 60 ms; p99 ≤ 150 ms`","numLines":160,"startLine":85,"totalLines":296}}}
