{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019Pjsg3SfoxpCQcecUgYvUg","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Multi-Agent Orchestration Pattern\n3\tdate: 2026-05-17\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Canonical Claude-implementer + Codex-reviewer spawn discipline for orchestrated work\n6\tblast_radius: dev/plans/prompts/*; .github/workflows/release.yml; release engineering; all multi-agent slices\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\tsupersedes:\n9\t  - dev/plans/0.6.0-Phase-9-Pack-5-performance-diagnostics.md § 0.1 (Pack-5-era invocation pattern)\n10\t  - dev/plans/prompts/01-orchestrator-resume.md § 4 (lifted here; resume doc now points back)\n11\t  - dev/plans/prompts/00-handoff-execute.md § 3-5 (Pack-5-era handoff)\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\t# Multi-Agent Orchestration Pattern\n15\t\n16\tCanonical pattern for orchestrated work: **Claude implements (writes\n17\tcode), Codex reviews (read-only verdict), main thread routes.**\n18\t\n19\tThis is the source of truth. Per-phase prompts cite this doc rather\n20\tthan re-declaring invocation patterns. AGENTS.md § 7 owns the\n21\tprinciples; this file owns the mechanics.\n22\t\n23\t## 1. Three-role separation\n24\t\n25\t| Role             | Who                                              | Tools                                                      | Output                                                                     |\n26\t| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n27\t| **Orchestrator** | Main thread (you). Always.                       | Bash, Edit, Read, Write. May spawn subagents.              | Plan files, cherry-picks, verdict promotions, commit decisions.            |\n28\t| **Implementer**  | Fresh `claude -p` process in a git worktree.     | Read, Edit, Write, Bash, Grep, Glob. **NEVER Task/Agent.** | Commits on a `phase-<id>-<ts>` branch + structured `<phase>-output.json`.  |\n29\t| **Reviewer**     | `codex exec` against the implementer's worktree. | Read-only sandbox.                                         | Verdict body (PASS / CONCERN / BLOCK) in log; main thread promotes to .md. |\n30\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d9c2010-470a-469e-a899-a4db3c31910c","uuid":"7a7be5d5-0ad3-4005-9b04-7c56d6235793","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:25:17.316Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/design/orchestration.md","content":"---\ntitle: Multi-Agent Orchestration Pattern\ndate: 2026-05-17\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Canonical Claude-implementer + Codex-reviewer spawn discipline for orchestrated work\nblast_radius: dev/plans/prompts/*; .github/workflows/release.yml; release engineering; all multi-agent slices\nstatus: locked\nsupersedes:\n  - dev/plans/0.6.0-Phase-9-Pack-5-performance-diagnostics.md § 0.1 (Pack-5-era invocation pattern)\n  - dev/plans/prompts/01-orchestrator-resume.md § 4 (lifted here; resume doc now points back)\n  - dev/plans/prompts/00-handoff-execute.md § 3-5 (Pack-5-era handoff)\n---\n\n# Multi-Agent Orchestration Pattern\n\nCanonical pattern for orchestrated work: **Claude implements (writes\ncode), Codex reviews (read-only verdict), main thread routes.**\n\nThis is the source of truth. Per-phase prompts cite this doc rather\nthan re-declaring invocation patterns. AGENTS.md § 7 owns the\nprinciples; this file owns the mechanics.\n\n## 1. Three-role separation\n\n| Role             | Who                                              | Tools                                                      | Output                                                                     |\n| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Orchestrator** | Main thread (you). Always.                       | Bash, Edit, Read, Write. May spawn subagents.              | Plan files, cherry-picks, verdict promotions, commit decisions.            |\n| **Implementer**  | Fresh `claude -p` process in a git worktree.     | Read, Edit, Write, Bash, Grep, Glob. **NEVER Task/Agent.** | Commits on a `phase-<id>-<ts>` branch + structured `<phase>-output.json`.  |\n| **Reviewer**     | `codex exec` against the implementer's worktree. | Read-only sandbox.                                         | Verdict body (PASS / CONCERN / BLOCK) in log; main thread promotes to .md. |\n","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":516}}}
