{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012wCaCavohPCLEmTtyMhi4i","type":"tool_result","content":"Based on the provided documentation:\n\n**(a) Mixing float[N] and bit[N] columns:**\nYes. The re-scoring example demonstrates this pattern: `\"create virtual table vec_movies using vec0(synopsis_embedding float[768], synopsis_embedding_coarse bit[768])\"` shows both vector types in one table.\n\n**(b) ALTER TABLE support:**\nNot addressed in this documentation excerpt.\n\n**(c) Auxiliary metadata + partition_key columns with vectors:**\nThe documentation mentions these features exist—there are navigation links to \"Metadata Columns,\" \"Partition Keys,\" and \"Auxiliary Columns\" sections—but specific syntax combining them with vector columns isn't shown in this content.\n\nThe only concrete binary-quantization column syntax provided is: `\"synopsis_embedding_coarse bit[768]\"` alongside a corresponding `float[768]` column for the full vector data."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d9c2010-470a-469e-a899-a4db3c31910c","uuid":"1b7c1a11-ef45-4c23-91cf-a61a0c8d1a58","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:25:46.089Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":50787,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"Based on the provided documentation:\n\n**(a) Mixing float[N] and bit[N] columns:**\nYes. The re-scoring example demonstrates this pattern: `\"create virtual table vec_movies using vec0(synopsis_embedding float[768], synopsis_embedding_coarse bit[768])\"` shows both vector types in one table.\n\n**(b) ALTER TABLE support:**\nNot addressed in this documentation excerpt.\n\n**(c) Auxiliary metadata + partition_key columns with vectors:**\nThe documentation mentions these features exist—there are navigation links to \"Metadata Columns,\" \"Partition Keys,\" and \"Auxiliary Columns\" sections—but specific syntax combining them with vector columns isn't shown in this content.\n\nThe only concrete binary-quantization column syntax provided is: `\"synopsis_embedding_coarse bit[768]\"` alongside a corresponding `float[768]` column for the full vector data.","durationMs":4343,"url":"https://alexgarcia.xyz/sqlite-vec/guides/binary-quant.html"}}
