{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016gf4WzBWaGXgPk1NAx9akM","type":"tool_result","content":"# sqlite-vec Virtual Table Syntax\n\nBased on the blog post, I cannot provide complete answers to all your questions.\n\n## Syntax Example\n\nThe article shows metadata and partition key columns but **does not include a bit[N] column example**. Here's what is demonstrated:\n\n```sql\ncreate virtual table vec_articles using vec0(\n  article_id integer primary key,\n  headline_embedding float[384],\n  year integer partition key,\n  news_desk text,\n  word_count integer,\n  pub_date text,\n  +headline text,\n  +url text\n);\n```\n\n## Unanswered Questions\n\nThe blog post does not specify:\n\n- **Maximum metadata columns or partition keys**: No limits are mentioned\n- **bit[N] column support**: The article only shows `float[384]` vector columns\n- **ALTER TABLE support**: This feature is not discussed\n\nThe post notes that metadata column types are expanding, stating \"More types like BLOBs, dates, and UUID/ULIDs are coming soon,\" but it doesn't address structural modification capabilities or hard limits on column counts."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d9c2010-470a-469e-a899-a4db3c31910c","uuid":"ac8882c0-e165-4418-aae1-80794084df41","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:25:55.029Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":54269,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# sqlite-vec Virtual Table Syntax\n\nBased on the blog post, I cannot provide complete answers to all your questions.\n\n## Syntax Example\n\nThe article shows metadata and partition key columns but **does not include a bit[N] column example**. Here's what is demonstrated:\n\n```sql\ncreate virtual table vec_articles using vec0(\n  article_id integer primary key,\n  headline_embedding float[384],\n  year integer partition key,\n  news_desk text,\n  word_count integer,\n  pub_date text,\n  +headline text,\n  +url text\n);\n```\n\n## Unanswered Questions\n\nThe blog post does not specify:\n\n- **Maximum metadata columns or partition keys**: No limits are mentioned\n- **bit[N] column support**: The article only shows `float[384]` vector columns\n- **ALTER TABLE support**: This feature is not discussed\n\nThe post notes that metadata column types are expanding, stating \"More types like BLOBs, dates, and UUID/ULIDs are coming soon,\" but it doesn't address structural modification capabilities or hard limits on column counts.","durationMs":3921,"url":"https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html"}}
